  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Cuisine: What are some unconventional ways to eat French fries?",
  "response": "French fries are a versatile and beloved comfort food, and there are many unconventional ways to enjoy them beyond the traditional dipping sauces. Here are some creative ideas:\n\n1. **Poutine**: Elevate your fries with cheese curds and hot gravy. You can also add toppings like pulled pork, bacon, or mushrooms.\n\n2. **Fries in a Burrito**: Wrap fries in a tortilla along with beans, cheese, and vegetables to create a hearty burrito.\n\n3. **Fries with Chocolate Sauce**: For a sweet twist, try dipping your fries in chocolate or drizzling them with melted chocolate for a dessert-like experience.\n\n4. **Fry Salad**: Top a bed of mixed greens with crispy fries, diced tomatoes, cheese, avocado, and your favorite dressing for a crunchy salad.\n\n5. **Fries Sandwich**: Use fries as a filling in a sandwich with your choice of proteins (like fried chicken or burgers) and sauces.\n\n6. **Fries Pizza**: Use French fries as a topping on a pizza, along with cheese, bacon, and ranch dressing for a decadent dish.\n\n7. **Fries with Salsa and Guacamole**: Swap out chips for fries when serving salsa and guacamole for a unique dip experience.\n\n8. **Fries with Curry**: Serve fries with a side of creamy curry sauce for an unexpected flavor combination.\n\n9. **Fries Tacos**: Add fries to a taco, along with your favorite toppings like meat, cheese, lettuce, and a drizzle of ranch or hot sauce.\n\n10. **Fries Breakfast Bowl**: Combine fries with scrambled eggs, cheese, and toppings like avocado or chorizo for a hearty breakfast.\n\n11. **Fries with Kimchi**: Top fries with saut\u00e9ed kimchi and a drizzle of sriracha or gochujang for a spicy Asian-inspired twist.\n\n12. **Fries Waffles**: Make a waffle batter with mashed potatoes and french fries mixed in, then cook it in a waffle iron for a crispy snack.\n\nThese ideas add a new twist to a popular favorite, making French fries a versatile base for countless delicious combinations!",
